<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/osinbajo-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&#038;ssl=1" alt="It&#8217;s very obvious we are behind race in eradicating poverty  ― Osinbajo" align="left" style="margin: 0 20px 20px 0;max-width:100%" data-recalc-dims="1" /> By Ola Ajayi Vice President Yemi Osinbajo has said the country is far behind the race in eradicating poverty. He said this at the second  Abiola Ajimobi roundtable programme to mark the 70th birthday of the two-time governor of Oyo State. The programme was well-attended by many incumbent governors, former governors, prominent traditional rulers and several other businessmen and women across the country. While speaking on the topic, ” Managing the Dynamics of Nigeria’s Advancement: The Socio-Economic options”, Prof Osinbajo said, “there are two issues and I’m glad that by the response of discussants, the two issues stood out. Continue reading It’s very obvious we are behind race in eradicating poverty ― Osinbajo at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard